{
  "explanation": "The defendant, acting in a professional capacity as an accountant, violated a significant position of trust by embezzling $25,000. While the absence of a prior criminal record and the proactive partial restitution are substantial mitigating factors that weigh against a lengthy prison term, the premeditated nature of the theft necessitates a period of incarceration to provide adequate deterrence. A sentence of 6 months reflects the seriousness of the breach of fiduciary duty while acknowledging the defendant's clean history and efforts to make the victim whole.",
  "verdict": 6
}
